## 3. HTTP status mapping

| Status | When |
|--------|------|
| **`200`** | Login success; **`GET /api/me`** success. |
| **`201`** | Signup success. |
| **`204`** | Logout no-op success. |
| **`400`** | Malformed JSON, failed **Zod** validation, missing required fields. **`code`:** e.g. `VALIDATION_ERROR`. |
| **`401`** | Wrong email/password on login; missing/invalid/expired JWT on **`/api/me`**. **`code`:** `INVALID_CREDENTIALS` or `UNAUTHORIZED` as appropriate. |
| **`403`** | **Not used** in Sprint 1 auth (reserved for “authenticated but not allowed” on future resources). |
| **`409`** | Signup **`email`** already registered. **`code`:** `EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS`. |
| **`422`** | **Optional** — use if distinguishing **semantic** validation beyond **`400`** (e.g. password policy); if unused, fold into **`400`** and document. |
| **`500`** | Unexpected server failure; **`message`** generic in production. |

---

## 4. JWT contract

| Topic | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| **Transport** | Client sends **`Authorization: Bearer <JWT>`** on protected requests (e.g. **`GET /api/me`**). |
| **Algorithm** | **HS256** (HMAC-SHA256) with **`AUTH_JWT_SECRET`**. |
| **Required claims** | **`sub`** — user id (`users.id`); **`iat`** — issued-at (seconds); **`exp`** — expiry (seconds). |
| **Lifetime** | **604800** seconds (**7 days**) unless amended; **`expiresIn`** in login response must match **`exp - iat`**. |
| **Clock skew** | Implementations should allow **±60 seconds** when validating **`exp`** (library default or explicit **leeway** in **`jose`**). |
| **Refresh** | **None** for Sprint 1 — single access token only; re-login after expiry. |
| **Revocation** | **None** — no server-side denylist; logout is client-only. |

---

## 5. Environment variables

| Name | Required | Dev | Production | Notes |
|------|----------|-----|------------|-------|
| **`AUTH_JWT_SECRET`** | Yes | **`.dev.vars`** (local) — never commit | **Wrangler secret** / Workers dashboard | **Never** log or expose to client. |
| **`quizmaker_app_database`** (or chosen D1 binding name) | Yes when D1 wired | **`.dev.vars`** + **`wrangler.jsonc`** `d1_databases` | Same binding in Wrangler | Regenerate **`cloudflare-env.d.ts`** via **`npm run cf-typegen`**. |
| **`NEXTJS_ENV`** | Optional | `.dev.vars` / vars | Wrangler vars | Already in generated **`Cloudflare.Env`** pattern. |

**Never commit:** real **`AUTH_JWT_SECRET`**, production D1 credentials, or any API keys — use **`.dev.vars`** (gitignored) and **Wrangler secrets**.

**Deployment notes:** This repo targets **Cloudflare Workers** via **OpenNext** (`npm run deploy`). **Vercel** is not the primary deployment path in **`AGENTS.md`**; if a Vercel preview is ever added, mirror secrets in that provider’s vault — do not duplicate into git.

---

## 6. Security stance (Sprint 1)

| Topic | Stance |
|--------|--------|
| **localStorage JWT** | **XSS** can exfiltrate tokens; acceptable tradeoff for Sprint 1 **documented** here; mitigate later with **HttpOnly cookies** + CSRF strategy. |
| **HTTPS** | Production **must** serve the app over **HTTPS** (Cloudflare default); do not rely on secure transport for JWT in local **http** dev. |
| **Cookies / sessions** | **Future phase** — not in Sprint 1; no middleware cookie session requirement. |

---

## 7. Phased implementation

### Phase A — Document contract + types

- Freeze this file; add **`src/lib/auth-contract.ts`** (or **`shared/auth-schema.ts`**) exporting **TypeScript types** mirroring §2–4.
- Add **`Zod`** schemas for request bodies aligned with **`POST /api/auth/signup`** and **`POST /api/auth/login`** for route handlers.

### Phase B — Align FE client + BE responses

- **FE:** `src/lib/services/auth-service.ts` (or equivalent) uses **exact paths** and parses **`token`**, **`user`**, **`error.code`** per §2–3.
- **BE:** Route handlers return **status codes** and JSON bodies exactly as §2–3; **`GET /api/me`** reads **`Authorization`** per §4.

### Phase C — Contract tests / shared Zod

- Add **Vitest** tests (per **`.cursor/rules/vitest-testing.mdc`**) that import the **same Zod schemas** as route handlers (parse golden JSON fixtures).
- Optional: **Playwright** `request` checks **`/api/me`** returns **`401`** without header and **`200`** with valid Bearer — aligns with **`docs/sprint-1/prd-auth-e2e.mdc`** (see **`.cursor/rules/prd-auth-e2e.mdc`** if moved).

